The following prefixes may be used for the "start" query parameter:  ge (Greater than or Equals) gt (Greater than) All unsupported prefixes are ignored during the search.  Supported date formats for the "start" query are as follows:  YYYY-MM-DD YYYY-MM YYYY The "start" query parameter is checked against the "context.period.start" property. If the context.period property fits the search criteria a DocumentReference resource is returned.  For example, assume we have a DocumentReference resource with a context.period.start = 2019-07-15 and context.period.end = 2019-07-30. A query of "start=gt2019-07&end=le2019-07" would return the resource as both the start and end query parameters clear checks with their respective context.period properties. A query of "start=gt2019-07-01&end=le2019-07-02" would NOT return the resource since the end query does NOT clear its check against context.period.end.  Example URI GET https://[subdomain]/v2/uscore/R4/DocumentReference?patient=7AC6963C-8108-4084-8B48-9FAE8A7D73EC&start=ge2015-07-01&end=le2017-08-20

Supported date formats for the "date" query are as follows:  YYYY-MM-DD YYYY-MM YYYY The "date" query parameter is checked against the "date" property.
